[Data by country, area, or territory for 7 Dec 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20DEC7_1638990357.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 13.9% of cases and 8.0% of deaths in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 97.80 million cases. The USA reported 39 928 cases over the last 24 hours. An additional 4 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Brazil, Argentina, Colombia, and Chile), and an additional 5 countries (Peru, Mexico, Bolivia, Venezuela, and Trinidad & Tobago) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 69.9% of daily case numbers and 73.7% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 89.56 million cases. Some countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Spain, Belgium (4 cases), Sweden, and Switzerland (9 cases), among others. A total of 22 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, with 9 reporting more than 10 000, 14 reporting over 1000 cases, and an additional 6 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 3.3% of daily case numbers and 3.7% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 16.87 million cases. Jordan (5811) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Iran (3356). Lebanon, Iraq, and Egypt reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Somalia and Djibouti did not report any cases for several days.

- The African region reported 2.9% of daily case numbers and 1.1% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 6.37 million cases. South Africa (6381) reported the highest number over the last 24 hours, followed by Eswatini (347), Ghana and Democratic Republic of Congo. A total of 17 countries/territories did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 7.0% of daily case numbers and 8.5% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 10.42 million cases. Viet Nam reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 14 591 cases), followed by South Korea, Malaysia, Australia, Laos, Singapore, and Philippines.

- The South-East Asia region reported 2.7% of the daily newly reported cases and 4.8% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 44.66 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 6000 cases during the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (3525). Nepal (272) and Indonesia (261) reported fewer than 500 cases. Bangladesh, Myanmar, Maldives, and Sri Lanka, among others, did not report cases for several days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 7 Dec 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

